# Conventions — {{.Project}}

> Style + naming + structural rules. Pull requests / agent sessions that
> violate these are rejected by the reviewer.

## Naming

- File names: lowercase, words separated by `_` (or `-` if the language
  prefers it). Match the dominant style of the language being used.
- Test files live next to the code they test (or in a sibling folder
  the language convention prescribes).

## Code structure

- Public API at the top of the file; helpers below.
- Every public function or type carries a doc comment that says *why*,
  not just *what*.
- Constants live at the top of their module.

## Errors

- Errors are returned / raised, never silently logged and discarded.
- Error messages are operator-readable: include the relevant id, path,
  or input fragment.

## Tests

- One test per acceptance criterion in `feature_list.json`.
- Test names describe the contract, not the implementation:
  `TestSaveSession_RejectsEmptyProject` not `TestSaveSession_3`.
- Tests use real fixtures (temp dirs, ephemeral DBs) where possible.
